{
  "texts": [
    "As a result of this simple CNN architecturem the study does not explore deeper or more complex architectures: these have the potential to further improve performance on challenging fossil images.",
    "Lastly, Ferreira-Chacua and Koeshidayatullah (2023) present an innovative DL workflow that combines the strengths of hierarchical vision transformers (SwinIR) and generative adversarial networks (StyleGAN2) for micropaleontological image analysis.",
    "By employing super-resolution techniques, the model enhances low-quality fossil images, achieving significant performance gains.",
    "Furthermore, Style-GAN2 generates synthetic images with a high FID score supporting fossil classification and segmentation tasks.",
    "This method introduces a practical framework for expanding dataset availability in micropaleontology, improving the efficiency of species recognition and morphological analysis."
  ]
}